               <p>I live in <placeName id="t17800510-55-crimeloc310">Ivy-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17800510-55-crimeloc310" type="placeName" value="Ivy-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17800510-55-crimeloc310" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17800510-55-off303 t17800510-55-crimeloc310"></join>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17800510-55-off308 t17800510-55-crimeloc310"></join>; these things were lost out of my kitchen window on the first of May, about eight in the evening; there was a wainscot box lost at the same time. I know nothing how they were taken.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I know nothing of it; it don't stand to-reason that I should be guilty of it, do you think if I had been and robbed a house I should go immediately and rob another?</p>
